olive oil
2 tin Chickpeas
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend

• Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Drain and rinse chickpeas.
• Pat chickpeas dry with paper towel.

TIP: Patting the chickpeas dry helps them crisp up in the oven!

• In a medium bowl, combine chickpeas, Mumbai spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil. Toss to coat.

• Divide chickpeas between two lined oven trays, arranging in a single layer.
• Roast until crisp and slightly brown around the edges, tossing halfway
through, 25-30 minutes.
• Remove from oven and set aside to cool. Season to taste.

• Transfer spiced roasted chickpeas to a serving bowl. Enjoy!

TIP: Chickpeas are best served immediately.